woolshed dance
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a party with live music and dance, held in a woolshed [popular in the 1920s and in the 1950s and 60s, and often hosted by parents of boarding-school students during holidays.]
Origin:
